Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Silenszug (Mythologie)" addressed to "Herrn Prof. Dr. phil. habil. Hans-Gerh. Evers Waldstrasse 43 D-6101 Traisa"

  • Extracts from different publications about 'Silenus'
  • Notes about the 'Satyr' in Dresden
  • Bibliographic references
  • Variuos notes and sketches
  • Article: 'Rubens' "Trunkener Silen"'
  • Reproductions of the 'Drunken Silenus', the 'Silenus March' and the 'Ecce Homo'
  • Subfolder (Annotation: "Rubens Silenszug"):
    • Notes about the 'Drunken Silenus' in Munich
    • Extracts from different publications about 'Silenus'
    • Bibliographic references
    • Reproduction of the 'Two Satyrs' and the 'Drunken Silenus'
    • Photo (from a newspaper) of an african family

Loose documentation in the Rubensdocumentation of the Rubenianum:

  • 5 photos of 'The Drunken Bacchus'
  • 1 photo of the back of the painting
